IOS ENGINEER
jobs_results.description:
Company Description

Yambla is a startup based in San Francisco and Belgium. We are revolutionizing the way companies innovate.

Even the largest companies have trouble innovating. Nokia, Kodak, BlackBerry and BlockBuster are just a few examples of thriving companies that went from hero to zero overnight due to a lack of innovation. It’s Yambla’s job to help companies stay ahead of the competition.

Here at Yambla we strongly believe employee engagement is the key to the success of any company, and it’s our mission to help companies build a culture of innovation by collecting ideas from employees, and turning them into value.

It’s a huge challenge and we can’t do this on our own – that’s why we need people like you!

Job Description

What you’ll be doing
• Imagine, implement, test, and iterate on new features
• Extending a mobile application that is used by some of the world’s largest brands
• Working in a diverse, dynamic environment that leverages multiple tools and languages
• Finding ways to remove obstacles, and weaknesses that slow you down

Qualifications
• Ability to pick any language or tool that is the right for the job and “run with it”
• You should have vast experience with iOS
• An understanding of object-oriented programming and software design patterns
• Excellent analytical and problem solving skills
• Strong intra-team communication and ability to express ideas
• Have opinions on how things should be planned, implemented, and maintained
• Excels in a pragmatic team that wants the best tools, cleanest code, and best product

Nice to haves:
• Dedication to unit testing, code review and other quality-oriented practices
• Experience with design

Additional Information

Compensation & Perks:
• Competitive salary
• Flexible working hours
• Beers!

If this sounds like you could excel in this environment, let’s have a chat! - Drop us an email at hello@yambla.com.

jobs_results.title: MOBILE DEVELOPER (H/F)
jobs_results.description:
Mobile Developer

Job Overview

New project do develop top cutting Edge Mobile app on both common platform IoS and Android and using adaptative UI for Android Auto and Apple CarPlay.

Responsibilities for Mobile Developer
• Identify and plan for new features
• Develop application programming interfaces (APIs) to support mobile functionality (based on AWS frameworks)
• Suggest and implement new mobile products, applications and protocols
• Remain up to date with the terminology, concepts and best practices for coding mobile apps
• Work closely with colleagues to constantly innovate app functionality and design
• Use and adapt existing web applications for apps
• Write unit and UI tests to identify malfunctions
• Communicate with users to understand their needs and experiences

Qualifications for Mobile Developer
• 3+ years of demonstrable experience
• Demonstrable portfolio of released applications on the App store or the Android market
• Extensive knowledge of at least one programming language like Swift and Amplify or Java
• Familiarity with OOP design principles
• Experience with third-party libraries and APIs (mostly AWS), Maps and géolocalisation services.
• Superior analytical skills with a good problem-solving attitude
• Ability to perform in a team environment
• Strong oral and written communication skills (English or French)
• Ability to interpret and follow technical plans

2 / AWS DevOps Architect

Job Overview

We are looking for a DevOps architect to manage the software development process and create an automated delivery pipeline that assists in building software more efficiently. The responsibilities of a DevOps architect include assessing, supporting, and implementing high-quality information technology architecture.

To be successful as a DevOps architect, you should demonstrate a leadership mindset, solid operational experience, and the ability to problem-solve. Ultimately, a top-notch DevOps Architect should have exceptional communication skills, be knowledgeable about the latest industry trends, and highly innovative.

You will design a scalable back office service to manage a mobile application , and manage the product life cycle.

AWS DevOps Architect Responsibilities :
• Facilitating the development process and operations.
• Identifying setbacks and shortcomings.
• Creating suitable DevOps channels across the organization.
• Establishing continuous build environments to speed up software development.
• Designing efficient practices, architecture design using AWS Services to automate and reduce operational costs
• Delivering comprehensive best practices.
• Managing and reviewing technical operations.
• Guiding the development team.

Qualifications for AWS DevOps Architect :
• Degree in computer science, information systems, or related field.
• AWS Solution architect and / or develops Certified
• Strong Skills in Python and java
• Previous experience working on a 24x7 cloud or SaaS operation team.
• Experience with infrastructure management and monitoring.
• Strong knowledge of DevOps Platform tooling ( Chef, Puppet, and Docker.)
• Strong knowledge on API, Database, localisation services
• Working knowledge of automation service provisioning and middleware configuration.
• Ability to work independently and as part of a team (mobile developers and UI designers).
• Strong analytical skills.

AWS Services to master for this project :

App mobile
• AWS Amplify
• AWS amplify Studio
• AWS cognito
• Location Service
• API Gateway
• AWS Device Farm
• AppSync

Back end
• Cloud Watch
• Cloud trail
• Route 59
• Aurora DB
• Time stream
• Quicksight (reporting)
• SageMaker
• AWS Lambda
• AWS ECS

jobs_results.title: Mobile applications developer
jobs_results.description:
Job Description

The number of customers in several countries enjoying our market leading integrated IT platform specifically for local shops, retail chains en couriers is exploding. The Connect24-7 platform allows them to serve their customers always and everywhere. That’s why we are looking to strengthen our experienced team with a passionate developer focusing on innovative mobile applications. The Connect 24-7 cash register en multi-channel management software connects the shop with its customers, suppliers and partners. Our courier software solutions allow courier companies to provide even more service to customers and end-receivers.

The right candidate will be part of a small but growing team following Agile software development practices. In this role you will be responsible to extend and improve existing mobile solutions. For this we are particularly looking for a passionate and highly motivated software developer with experience in designing and building high performance mobile applications.

Requirements
• Bachelor/Master in Computer Science or Informatics, or equal by experience
• Experience with c# and Windows Phone, Java and Android or cocoa and iOS apps
• Good understanding of REST API’s
• Experience with Android en iOS development is highly appreciated
• Good English oral and written skills, since our team consists of several nationalities
• Entrepreneurial spirit

Strong problem solving and critical thinking ability with structured and (object-) oriented solutions Ability to work well under pressure, meet strict deadlines and communicate Think ahead of (y)our competitors but listen even better to (the problems of) (y)our customers!

Application Instructions

If you would like to receive more information please contact us or if you would like to apply immediately, please submit your resume to HR@iButler.be citing Mobile Developer in the subject of your message. Please also elaborate on your experience working on relevant projects. We thank all applicants in advance for their interest in iButler Group!
